parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience issues with the brakes, steering, and other essential systems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

loses power
or experiences issues with the brakes
steering
and other essential systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes make a wearing metal noise
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
or the brake light is always on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to become stuck or difficult to open, leading to safety issues.
symptoms: The door locks do not function electronically
or the door locks become stuck or difficult to open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the navigation and infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The navigation display fails
the backup camera does not function
or the HVAC control malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
or the vehicle experiences issues with the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy incorrectly or not deploy at all, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light is always illuminated
or the airbag system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or slip while shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips
hesitates
or fails to engage; delayed or rough shifting; vehicle jerks or lurches while shifting; loss of power while accelerating; transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; clutch pedal sticks to the floor; clutch pedal does not return to its normal position; clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position; clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy; brake pedal sticks to the floor; brake pedal does not return to its normal position; brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position; brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure; vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalls while driving; engine stalls while idling; engine stalls when accelerating; engine stalls when decelerating; engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power steering and brakes, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often when making turns or driving at low speeds (15-40 mph)
and may restart after a brief delay. The vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and brakes
and the dashboard warning lights may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, premature wear, and potential engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil without warning
often without any noticeable symptoms or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause inconvenience and discomfort, especially during hot weather.
symptoms: The air conditioning compressor fails
often without warning
and may not function properly or at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An exhaust smell or leak can be a safety concern, as it may indicate a potential hazard from carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: The vehicle emits a strong exhaust smell
often when starting the engine or at idle
which may be overwhelming and potentially hazardous.
